id: pm-45mb
title: "GH-534: no-op update reports phantom changed_fields in --json while TOON reports empty, and changed_field_count is always null in JSON"
description: "A no-op pm update (field set to its current value) emits changed_fields:['title'] in --json but an empty changed_fields in TOON — the two formats disagree about whether anything changed; agents keying off JSON see phantom mutations. Additionally changed_field_count is computed for TOON but left null in the JSON envelope. Fix: compute changed_fields once from the actual before/after diff and share it across both renderers (uniform output contract — pm-srns territory), and populate changed_field_count as a number (0 for no-op). Check update-many/close envelopes for the same divergence at fix time."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 2
tags[4]: agent-ux,cli,gh-issue,json-output
